Communicate with staff, volunteers, members, and the people you serve. Coordinate with local health officials to communicate closure decisions, alterations to services, and the possible COVID-19 exposure. CFBOs play a vital role in maintaining community morale and cohesion, especially if large gatherings and other community assemblies are cancelled. People will need to be able to receive timely, reliable information from their religious and community leaders.
In such a circumstance, it is critical to maintain confidentiality of the person who is a confirmed COVID-19 case.
