The 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic was confirmed to have spread to Japan on 16 January 2020 from China.[3]
On 27 February 2020, Prime Minister Shinzo Abe requested that all Japanese elementary, junior high, and high schools close until early April to help contain the virus.[4] The pandemic has been a concern for the 2020 Summer Olympics, which has been postponed to 2021 because of it.[5] The Japanese government has been taking extra precautions to help minimise the outbreak's impact.[6]
