A new coronavirus that emerged in China late last year has spread to more than 170 countries on six continents, with the World Health Organization (WHO) declaring the pathogen a pandemic. 
The death toll from the virus has surged past 30,000 and the number of reported cases is more than 666,000 globally, according to data compiled by Johns Hopkins University. Some 141,000 have so far recovered.
